{"/service/ndnp/mohi/batch_mohi_beetlebailey_ver01/data/sn88068010/00294556102/1908012401/0193.xml":{"full_text":"if\nE are going to offer the people of KEYTESVILLE AND CHARITON COUNTY a Great Opportunity\nto Save Money on Dependable Merchandise, Last fall we bought much heavier than usual, the warm\nweather which we have had and the brief financial panic causes us to be overstocked for this season of the\nyear. In order to meet our obligations we have got to have money and, in order to get money, we are offer\ningevery thing in this stock at Greatly Reduced Prices in some cases less than the goods cost us laid down at\nKeytesville depot. This is no hot air talk,but a straight business proposition and a call at our store will convince- -you\nthat we are doing just what we say we are.\nENDING SATURDAY, FEBRUARY 1, 1908,\nWe will offer for sale every article of merchandise in this store at prices you cannot match anywhere. Nothing will be reserved, but the knife has gone into the\nprice of every particle we carry. If Wc pledge you our word tqat not one article of bankrupt stock has been brought in for this sale, but it is just what we claim it\nto be a genuine, bona fide, cut-price sale in order to reduce our stock and meet our bills. Another feature of this sale to which we must call attention is that it is\nfor spot cash. ffi Nothing will be allowed to go out of the store until it is paid for, for we could not afford to sell goods at these prices and charge them, besides\nthe purpose of'this salejis to raise ready money.\nAs o hiDtp) show how we are cutting prices throughout the store, see the following\nsc..\nDress Goods\nAll $1.25 Dress Goods,\nAll 1.00\nAll .75\nAll .50\nnow .87\n.75\n.50\n.38J\nMen's Dress Shirts\nAll 1.00 Dress Shirts,\nAll .75\nA t\na.\nnow .75\n.50\n.40\ntt\nit\nShoes\nMen's 5.00 Crossett Shoes,\n4.00 u\n3.50\n3.00 '5\n2.50\n2.00\nnow $3.75\n3.25\n2.90\n2.35\n2.00\n1.75\ntt\ntt\nHats\nAll $3.00 Thoroughbred Hats,\nAll 2.50\nAll 2.00\nAll 1.50\nnow $2.25\ni:75\n1.50\n1.15\na\nWool Blankets\nAll-wool 11-4 7.00 Blankets,\nAll-wool 11-4 6.00\nAll-wool 11-4 5.00\nAll-wool 10-4 4.50\nnow $5.50\n-4.50\n4.00\n3.35\nUnderwear\nAll 1.00 Garments,\nAll .75\nAll .50\nnowf .75\n.50\n.38y2\nThe above is just a sample of the way prices are cut on everything in the store. Nothing is held in reserve. We are not making leaders of anything, but are genuinely\ncutting prices throughout the stock. The warm weather has left us with a great deal too much stock on our hands and it must be turned into cash just as quickly as\npossible.! In many instances you can buy these goods eheaper than we could buy them from the wholesale houses.\nPIT ft TO\nII HD\nPR\nnn\nid\n11 HTO\nUJUJCj.iu\n(D0n\nVILLE. MO\nBe\nn min d: Th is Sale is for Spot Cash.\ntfei ill F\nrapy U sit\nRemember the date:\nO rt\nmatmisiiv i\nLJ","height":"33156","width":"24076"}}
